<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
<title>CSS Test: page properties: border properties</title>
<link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
<link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#page-properties"/>
<meta name="flags" content="paged" />
<meta name="assert" content="Border properties defined in CSS2.1 apply to margin boxes."/>
<style type="text/css">
	@page {
		@top-left-corner {
			margin-top: 0.5in;
			border-top: 6pt solid green;
			content: "";
		}
		@top-left {
			margin-top: 0.5in;
			border-top: 6pt solid green;
			content: "";
		}
		@top-center {
			margin-top: 0.5in;
			border-top: 6pt solid green;
			content: "";
		}
		@top-right {
			margin-top: 0.5in;
			border-top: 6pt solid green;
			content: "";
		}
		@top-right-corner {
			margin-top: 0.5in;
			border-top: 6pt solid green;
			content: "";
		}
	}
</style>
</head>
<body>
	<p>When printed, there must be a green bar running across the page, about one half inch down from the top.</p>
</body>
</html>